23 service is provided or at a later date. A provider shall not refuse to provide a service if a
24 participant is unable to pay a required payment. If it is the routine business practice of a
25 provider to terminate future services to an individual with an unclaimed debt, the provider may
26 include uncollected co-payments under this practice. Providers who elect not to undertake the
27 provision of services based on a history of bad debt shall give participants advance notice and a
28 reasonable opportunity for payment. A provider, representative, employee, independent
29 contractor, or agent of a pharmaceutical manufacturer shall not make co-payment for a
30 participant. This subsection shall not apply to other qualified children, pregnant women, or blind
31 persons. If the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services does not approve the MO HealthNet
32 state plan amendment submitted by the department of social services that would allow a provider
33 to deny future services to an individual with uncollected co-payments, the denial of services
34 shall not be allowed. The department of social services shall inform providers regarding the
35 acceptability of denying services as the result of unpaid co-payments.
